{"id":5811,"date":"2021-05-26T10:05:59","date_gmt":"2021-05-26T08:05:59","guid":{"rendered":"http:\/\/154.0.202.153\/?page_id=5811"},"modified":"2024-04-27T12:37:24","modified_gmt":"2024-04-27T10:37:24","slug":"standing-committee-on-transport-infrastructure-and-housing","status":"publish","type":"page","link":"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/standing-committee-on-transport-infrastructure-and-housing\/","title":{"rendered":"Standing Committee on Transport, Infrastructure and Housing"},"content":{"rendered":"<p>[vc_row][vc_column][vc_tta_accordion][vc_tta_section title=&#8221;Functions&#8221; tab_id=&#8221;1614675935370-0134560d-4d1d&#8221;][vc_column_text]<\/p>\n<ol>\n<li>to deal with questions falling within the ambit of Offices, Ministries, Agencies, and Public Enterprises dealing with national planning, works and transport, urban and rural development, housing and sanitation;<\/li>\n<li>to scrutinise regional development policies and advise the Council thereon;<\/li>\n<li>to scrutinise legislation on Regional and Local Authorities and advise the Council on such matters as the Committee deems necessary;<\/li>\n<li>to liaise with bodies representing the interests of Regional Councils and Local Authorities;<\/li>\n<li>to promote the development, upgrading and maintenance of road infrastructure in rural areas;<\/li>\n<li>\u00a0to promote compliance with Istanbul Declaration on Human Settlements and UN Habitat Agenda;<\/li>\n<li>to monitor budget implementation of Offices, Ministries and Agencies falling within the Standing Committee\u2019s ambit;<\/li>\n<li>to monitor the implementation of the decentralization process on matters falling within the ambit of the Standing Committee; and<\/li>\n<li>to perform any other function as may be referred to it by the Council.<\/li>\n<\/ol>\n<p>[\/vc_column_text][\/vc_tta_section][vc_tta_section title=&#8221;Clerks&#8221; tab_id=&#8221;1622709961976-6f3610f4-d109&#8243;][vc_column_text]<\/p>\n<table>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td width=\"130px